ConocoPhillips Indonesia Jobs: Business Apprentice | Operation Apprentice | Petrotech Apprentice
ConocoPhillips is the world’s largest independent E&P company based on production and proved reserves. Headquartered in Houston, Texas, ConocoPhillips had operations and activities in 27 countries, $54 billion in annual revenue, $118 billion of total assets, and approximately 18,400 employees as of Dec. 31, 2013. Production from continuing operations averaged 1,502 MBOED in 2013, and preliminary proved reserves were 8.9 billion BOE as of Dec. 31, 2013.
ADVERTISEMENT
Employees across the globe focus on fulfilling our core SPIRIT Values of safety, people, integrity, responsibility, innovation and teamwork. And we apply the characteristics that define leadership excellence in how we engage each other, collaborate with our teams, and drive the business.
Business Apprentice - Jakarta
Business Apprentice is ConocoPhillips Indonesia development acceleration programs for university fresh graduates with business and some engineering background. The purpose of this program is to "identify, attract, develop and retain consistently exceptional performers who have the potential to become future leaders of the Company.
You will participate in an intensive development programs for 1-2 years that will sharpen your technical and soft skills to prepare you to become the globally competitive ConocoPhillips employees. The programs include on the job training, classroom training, practical experience, coaching and mentoring by experienced personnel. Upon successful completion of the programs, you will become employees of ConocoPhillips Indonesia and will also have future opportunities in other business units of ConocoPhillips globally.
Requirements
Fresh graduates (bachelor / master degree) who have / will completed at least bachelor degree prior October 1, 2014; or those with maximum of 2 years relevant working experience.
Majoring in Accounting, Finance, Management, Tax, Law, Industrial Engineering, and Mechanical Engineering with minimum GPA of 3.30 of 4.00 scales or 82.5 of 100 scale.
Fluent in English (oral and writing).
Highly motivated, strong analytical skill and problem solving capabilities.
Operation Apprentice - Jakarta
Operations Apprentice Program is an accelerated development program designed to meet the demand of qualified production operators and technicians. It is designed to meet both current and future challenges of ConocoPhillips Indonesia. This will be done through an extensive training and development programs to equipped apprentices with an understanding about Oil and Gas Industry and ConocoPhillips operations in Indonesia.  This program will include challenging trainings and job assignment in ConocoPhillips operations where apprentice could apply their academic knowledge to real-business situations.
Requirements
Fresh graduates (Diploma 3) who have / will completed prior to October 1, 2014; or those with maximum of 2 years relevant working experience.
Majoring in Chemical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Electronics Engineering, Instrument Engineering, and Mechanical Engineering.
Minimum GPA of 3.00 of 4.00 scales or 75.00 of 100 scales.
Fluent in English (oral and writing).
Highly motivated, strong analytical skill and problem solving capabilities.
Petrotech Apprentice
PetroTech Apprentice is ConocoPhillips Indonesia development acceleration programs for university fresh graduates with petro-technical and engineering background. It is a comprehensive acceleration program for recruiting and early-career development of upstream geoscientists and engineers. PetroTech Apprentice aims to identify, attract, develop and retain high and exceptional performers who have the potential to become future technical experts of the company.
You will participate in an intensive development programs for 1-2 years that will sharpen your technical and soft skills to prepare you to become the globally competitive ConocoPhillips employees. The programs include engineering academy, on the job training, classroom training, practical experience, coaching and mentoring by experienced personnel. Upon successful completion of the programs, you will become employees of ConocoPhillips Indonesia and will also have future opportunities in other business units of ConocoPhillips globally.
Requirements
Fresh graduates (bachelor / master degree) who have / will completed at least bachelor degree prior to October 1, 2014; or those with maximum of 2 years relevant working experience.
Majoring in Petroleum Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Chemical Engineering, Geology, and Geophysicist.
ADVERTISEMENT
Minimum GPA of 3.20 of 4.00 scales or 80.00 of 100 scales.
Fluent in English (oral and writing).
Highly motivated, strong analytical skill and problem solving capabilities.
Note: Attach your CV (including photo & latest academic transcript) in pdf or Microsoft word format not more than 300 kilobyte. In order to be considered for this position you must complete the entire application process, which includes answering all prescreening questions and providing your eSignature on or before the requisition closing date of May 25, 2014. ConocoPhillips is an equal opportunity employer.
